Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:06.56,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}Index's perfect memorization isn't a life-threatening condition even if her memories aren't erased in one year periods.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.04,0:00:10.36,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That means The Church lied to Stiyl and Kanzaki?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:19.15,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Successfully constructed the most effective weapon against the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:24.70,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Now initiating local weapon, "St. George's Sanctuary".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.70,0:00:26.68,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Proceeding to destroy intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:34.95,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,500)\pos(1158,493)}#06 Imagine\NBreaker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.41,0:00:37.70,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I forgot to ask one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:40.16,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...the reason why a non-esper like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.59,0:00:42.79,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...can't use magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.68,0:01:13.57,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.78,0:01:15.99,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Why can she... use magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.10,0:01:18.45,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:24.16,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That Index can't use magic... was simply The Church's lie!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.01,0:01:27.29,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.93,0:01:31.84,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact Index would die if her memories weren't erased in one year periods is a big fat lie, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.79,0:01:36.82,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Her brain is just filled with The Church's magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.34,0:01:42.61,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Erase all that and there wouldn't be any need to erase her memories anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.99,0:01:44.59,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.16,0:01:46.72,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.72,0:01:49.69,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...those people that forced her to take on the harsh role of being the index of prohibited books...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:54.82,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...would kindly tell lower level members like you the entire truth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.60,0:01:59.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,If not, then ask Index personally!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.45,0:02:05.04,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,St. George's Sanctuary does not seem to be effective against the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.53,0:02:09.83,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Switching to other spells and proceeding with the destruction of the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.31,0:02:22.35,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Fortis931!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.97,0:02:37.48,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need a vague possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:42.16,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If her memories are erased, then at least she'll still have her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:45.20,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill anyone for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.71,0:02:47.31,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy whatever is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:48.62,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,That was my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.07,0:02:51.29,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,One that I made long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:55.86,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,"At least", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.86,0:02:59.57,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong; screw that kind of pathetic thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:02.89,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Just answer me one thing, magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:05.85,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to save Index?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.43,0:03:09.10,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You guys have been waiting for this, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.49,0:03:12.09,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where you don't need to take away Index's memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.09,0:03:14.27,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where you don't need to be Index's enemies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.97,0:03:18.28,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where everyone is smiling and that everyone wants...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:20.58,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...that leads to the best happy ending!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.10,0:03:24.35,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You've been waiting all your lives for this, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:25.89,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,For this development?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:29.37,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What have you guys been clenching your teeth all this time for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:35.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you swear you'd save this one girl with your own hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:38.64,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You'd like to be the main characters of the story, too, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.10,0:03:41.78,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Quit being content staying a side character!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.22,0:03:46.68,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you want to put your lives on the line and protect this one girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:49.39,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.71,0:03:51.35,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't even begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:55.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Quit getting depressed in this kinda long prologue!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.65,0:03:57.59,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You can reach her if you stretch your hand out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.53,0:04:01.28,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this thing started already, magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:10.16,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Salvare000!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:31.64,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What's... this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:34.18,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,This is... Dragon's Breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.18,0:04:37.46,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,It's akin to St. George's dragon's attack according to legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:41.63,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,If you even come in contact with one feather, you'll be doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.19,0:04:49.72,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.54,0:04:56.25,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Go, esper!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:02.51,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.95,0:05:05.03,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 6, Verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.57,0:05:07.39,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed new enemy soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:09.62,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Changing battle logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.30,0:05:12.35,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Commencing search trace of the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.56,0:05:14.48,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:19.94,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Prioritizing the destruction of the most problematic enemy, Kamijyo Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.20,0:05:34.23,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:37.23,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 22, Verse 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.91,0:05:40.67,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Succeeded in reverse engineering of flame spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:45.34,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed to be a distorted interpretation of Christian doctrines, described by runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:49.30,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Constructing an anti-Christian weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.85,0:05:56.39,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Moving St. George's Sanctuary to Stage 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:59.02,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Eli Eli Lama Sabachthani?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:59.02,Note,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?" (Matthew 27:45-46)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.61,0:06:01.70,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:12.99,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:18.57,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,If this world really is functioning through Your system...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.67,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.20,0:06:23.55,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll destroy that illusion first!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.89,0:06:33.67,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,War... ning...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:38.55,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Final Chapter... Verse... 0...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.39,0:06:42.28,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Necklace"... suffered fatal destruction...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:47.53,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Regeneration impo-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.05,0:07:55.31,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious ray of light and one surveillance satellite destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:08:01.81,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,You and two others that don't possess any ID came into this city, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.18,0:08:04.70,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,So, you guys don't have anything to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.70,0:08:05.70,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:11.63,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That letter seems to be from the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:24.08,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I think that it's not for you, but for that kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:24.75,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.18,0:08:29.92,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Salutations are worthless so let me skip that."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:33.91,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,You've really done it, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.91,0:08:35.72,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...was what I wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.72,0:08:40.54,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...but if I really voiced out my personal emotions, even cutting down all the trees in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:43.35,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...wouldn't make enough paper for that purpose, so I'll refrain from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.23,0:08:48.67,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,As the least of courtesy I can show for your assistance in all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:52.17,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain the complete situation concerning you and her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:08:59.57,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,The English Purist Church wished to immediately take her back,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:03.46,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,but when we asked for an explanation for lying to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.46,0:09:05.98,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,they suddenly decided to maintain the current status quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.58,0:09:09.73,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure it's more accurate to say they want to monitor developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.26,0:09:15.82,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Me, personally, I can't tolerate any second you're around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.48,0:09:23.22,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, this doesn't exactly mean we're giving her to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.36,0:09:31.78,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,We will collect information and retrieve her once we have gathered proper equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:35.44,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my style to kill you in your sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.87,0:09:38.40,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"...so clean your neck and wait for us."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.85,0:09:46.64,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,A rather extreme friend you have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:50.14,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he mixed in some liquid explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:04.69,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be faster if you'd go see that kid in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:06.68,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.46,0:10:11.63,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it'd be rude to be shocked when you do see him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:13.85,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,so let me give you a quick and dirty lesson #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.10,0:10:32.84,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.37,0:10:57.34,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:07.33,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.03,0:11:14.04,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come to the wrong room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:21.09,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That's memory destruction, rather than memory loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:23.79,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Memory destruction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.79,0:11:26.19,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't forget his memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.19,0:11:29.39,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,but rather his brain cells were physically destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:32.81,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he'd remember anything to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.53,0:11:34.93,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.93,0:11:38.16,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Did they open up his noggin and use a stun gun on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.11,0:11:45.73,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:48.53,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:51.60,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be in great pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.82,0:11:55.79,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.79,0:11:56.82,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.31,0:11:59.90,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:02.72,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.33,0:12:06.14,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Do we know each other by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.23,0:12:09.63,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.32,0:12:13.58,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,We first met on the balcony of your student dormitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:17.68,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I lived in a student dormitory?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.77,0:12:21.12,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.78,0:12:26.28,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,My Walking Church got destroyed by your right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.76,0:12:28.92,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What's... a walking church?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.46,0:12:31.12,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Some kind of walking club?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:34.26,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.24,0:12:39.71,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,You fought against magicians for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.56,0:12:42.92,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Whose name is Touma?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.84,0:12:46.28,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma... don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:48.38,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Index...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.38,0:12:53.10,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Index... loved you, Touma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:57.54,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, what's index?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.00,0:12:59.85,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's not a person's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:02.73,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did I have a pet dog or cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.72,0:13:16.30,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,JUST KIDDING!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.14,0:13:18.84,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:28.43,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting all emotional for being called a dog or cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.43,0:13:30.14,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You must be that type.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:31.85,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You like collars?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.85,0:13:35.64,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Are you requesting me to do that kind of stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.86,0:13:37.94,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:43.62,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, weren't your brain cells blown away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.62,0:13:45.15,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you forget everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.86,0:13:50.24,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You sound as if it'd be better if I did forget everything, yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:52.44,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.91,0:13:55.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,According to that frog-faced doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:13:57.66,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,my brain cells got destroyed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.32,0:14:01.76,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I should've lost my memories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:04.13,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Should've"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.63,0:14:05.99,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.99,0:14:08.86,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The damage was caused by magic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.30,0:14:11.11,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:14.22,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I touched my head with my right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:18.35,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...and directed Imagine Breaker towards myself and voila.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:20.73,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine... Breaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:22.57,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The name for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.97,0:14:25.01,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the doctors called it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.01,0:14:27.36,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,In simple terms, before the damage reached the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:31.14,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I just needed to dispel the magical damage, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.66,0:14:37.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,And look at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:41.25,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,For all the problems you caused to others this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:45.63,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,you can take a good long look at yourself in the mirror, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.89,0:14:47.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:15.30,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.30,0:15:17.49,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to die... really...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.77,0:15:25.46,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,But, was that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.11,0:15:31.26,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't remember anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.85,0:15:36.71,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I told you word for word what I heard from those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:45.74,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I... just didn't want that girl to cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.47,0:15:48.80,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's what crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:56.28,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what this emotion is,\Nand I'm sure I won't ever remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.88,0:16:01.68,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,But that's what crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:05.96,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, I still remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:11.34,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Your memories are dead, along with your brain cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.19,0:16:15.30,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,No information remains in your brain, or should, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.17,0:16:20.55,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Then, where are your memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:24.66,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:30.86,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,My heart, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:49.14,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,Two weeks have passed since the interruption of communication with artificial satellite, Orihime-01,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.14,0:16:52.59,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,yet there is still no indication as to when communications will be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:57.70,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,It has been decided the board will have immediate discussions concerning future goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.91,0:17:13.72,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl Magnus.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:21.35,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Every single person that comes here looks at how I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:23.23,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,...and reacts in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.22,0:17:30.07,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,"There shouldn't be a need to let a human do something machines do," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.97,0:17:31.85,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.25,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,General Superintendent Aleister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.86,0:17:40.45,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you already know the reason for being recalled from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.41,0:17:43.08,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,The situation has become complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.77,0:17:45.93,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,"Deep Blood", correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:49.31,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Its existence is uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.31,0:17:55.15,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,A girl possessing the power to kill "a certain organism", whose existence is not even certain, is being imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:18:02.59,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,What has complicated matters is that you magicians,\Nwho shouldn't be within this city, have taken part in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:04.31,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Magicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:09.16,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,It is rather easy to terminate a magician or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.32,0:18:12.67,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,That is not the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:14.91,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,The issue is that we, the science side,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.91,0:18:18.13,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,will end up defeating the magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.60,0:18:25.83,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Because the science side and the magic side both hold their own exclusive technologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:28.11,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,the balance of the world exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:35.23,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,It is rather obvious what would happen if Academy City, which governs all espers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.10,0:18:38.27,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,insists that it has defeated magicians, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.58,0:18:40.61,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.65,0:18:47.21,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If I, a magician, take out someone from the magic side,\Nno one would have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.21,0:18:48.55,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:56.59,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,And I also possess a natural enemy of magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:59.47,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine Breaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:05.14,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,But is it not dangerous to be using an esper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:06.88,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,There are no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:08.89,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He is Level 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:10.29,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,A "powerless" person.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.13,0:19:13.67,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He does not possess any valuable information.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.19,0:19:19.78,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,There are no fears that our information would be leaked by him accompanying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.21,0:19:23.99,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me... to partner up with that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:27.49,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He knows your technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.49,0:19:29.95,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,but has no intelligence to re-create it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:33.83,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, you don't have to worry\Nthat your information might be leaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:36.76,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.46,0:19:43.26,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.18,0:19:48.61,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...does "Deep Blood" really exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.51,0:19:52.85,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If it really does exist, then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.59,0:19:58.61,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,...that the "certain organism" that it needs to kill also exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.64,0:20:00.82,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Vampires...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:07.86,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,I believe occult affairs are not\Nour area of expertise, but yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:09.86,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.55,0:20:15.37,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,If Deep Blood proves the existence of vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.85,0:20:20.78,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,then whose existence will the Imagine Breaker prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.72,0:20:27.72,Preview,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.09,0:20:28.69,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The Alchemist, Aureolus Izzard's target, the Deep Blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:30.40,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That girl being imprisoned in Misawa cram school is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:33.32,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, magician?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.60,0:20:35.27,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Science Worship".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.77,0:20:37.65,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,When science and magic cross paths,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.65,0:20:38.84,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,this epic will begin!
